### 2026-04-06T02:00:00Z — TASK-4.1 COMPLETE

**Agent:** Research Worker
**Action:** EU IVDR regulatory landscape analysis completed
**Details:**

- Researched EU IVDR (Regulation 2017/746) impact on genetic testing companies
- Key findings: IVDR applies from May 26, 2022, replacing IVDD
- Risk-based classification: Most genetic tests fall under Class C (moderate-high risk) requiring Notified Body involvement
- Extended transition via Regulation 2024/1860: Class D to 2027, Class C to 2028, Class B/A-sterile to 2029
- Article 5(5) health institution exemption narrower than historical LDT practices
- Blueprint Genetics positioned well: WES already CE marked, ISO 15189 accredited
- Sources: S-020 (EU Commission MDCG), S-021 (BSI Group)
- Output: Section 5.1 of research_synthesis.md (~900 words)

